Not the dolls. I meant
that thing over there.

12
00:02:12,958 --> 00:02:14,250
The machine?

13
00:02:27,750 --> 00:02:30,958
Oh, that's right. I stayed
up late drinking sake in

14
00:02:31,041 --> 00:02:35,708
the kitchen last night... And
then... Mom carried me to bed.

15
00:02:37,875 --> 00:02:39,250
A dream?

16
00:02:42,958 --> 00:02:47,166
Hey Mom, guess what? Had
a dream about you last night.

17
00:02:47,250 --> 00:02:51,625
But if that was a dream, how
did I get back to my own room?

18
00:02:51,708 --> 00:02:53,208
I don't remember that at all.

19
00:02:54,125 --> 00:02:56,250
You're up early
this morning, Tsukimi!

20
00:02:56,333 --> 00:02:57,958
Hey. Yeah, g'morning.

21
00:02:58,041 --> 00:03:01,166
Got two words for you
last night. Rock Star.

22
00:03:01,250 --> 00:03:04,416
That brings up a good
question. Do rock stars usually

23
