55
00:04:19,083 --> 00:04:21,958
I know that... but it
looks like a cool dress to me.

56
00:04:22,041 --> 00:04:24,500
If we make something that
looks like this, it'll sell.

57
00:04:24,583 --> 00:04:27,291
It's too cute not to! We'll
take over the fashion world!

58
00:04:27,375 --> 00:04:29,125
We'll save Amamizu-kan!

59
00:04:29,208 --> 00:04:32,083
I want to make this...
out of this, right here.

60
00:04:32,166 --> 00:04:33,541
And I want Chieko to do it.

61
00:04:33,625 --> 00:04:37,250
Sorry... I can only
make traditional clothing.

62
00:04:37,333 --> 00:04:40,166
And I only use this
machine to stitch yukata.

63
00:04:40,250 --> 00:04:42,916
Yukata... You made that, too?

64
00:04:43,000 --> 00:04:45,291
Whoa! Chieko... you rock!

65
00:04:45,375 --> 00:04:48,916
You're so sweet but anyone could
do it, it's nothing special.

66
00:04:49,000 --> 00:04:49,958
How do you do it?

67
00:04:50,041 --> 00:04:52,750
It's really very
easy. I'll show you.

68
00:04:52,833 --> 00:04:55,333
Watch, I just started
making a new kimono for

69
00:04:55,416 --> 00:04:58,541
Midoriko this morning and
I'm nearly finished with it.

70
00:04:59,375 --> 00:05:00,708
So fast!

71
00:05:00,791 --> 00:05:02,708
The type of stitching used
in traditional clothing is

72
00:05:02,791 --> 00:05:04,708
refined from a technique
passed down in Japan

73
00:05:04,791 --> 00:05:07,250
since ancient times, exclusively
using straight lines.

74
00:05:07,333 --> 00:05:09,666
Western-style clothing is
all curved lines designed to

75
00:05:09,750 --> 00:05:11,125
accommodate the
wearer's body shape,

76
00:05:11,208 --> 00:05:13,166
it's completely different,
even on a conceptual level.

77
00:05:13,250 --> 00:05:15,125
You're sewing without
even looking at your hands!

78
00:05:15,208 --> 00:05:16,875
Come on, I know
you can do this!

79
00:05:16,958 --> 00:05:18,708
No, no, no, no, no, no,
no, no, no, no, no, no!

80
00:05:18,791 --> 00:05:20,250
Why not?

81
00:05:20,333 --> 00:05:22,041
I already told you, Japanese
and Western sewing come from

82
00:05:22,125 --> 00:05:23,666
completely different
schools of thought.

83
00:05:23,750 --> 00:05:25,791
Skills don't matter if they're
in a different discipline.

84
00:05:25,875 --> 00:05:27,666
I'll give you an analogy,
it's like you're asking

85
00:05:27,750 --> 00:05:29,875
a sushi chef from
Tokyo to make a fine roux

86
00:05:29,958 --> 00:05:32,375
like a French chef in Paris
would. It can't be done.

87
00:05:32,458 --> 00:05:34,541
You're a sewing
savant, don't you see?!

88
00:05:34,625 --> 00:05:37,583
The point is, I can't possibly
make something so complicated.

89
00:05:37,666 --> 00:05:40,250
If I help, it'll only
be with stitching.

90
00:05:40,333 --> 00:05:43,500
You'll just have to make the
rest of it work yourselves.

91
00:05:43,583 --> 00:05:45,666
"Make it work," she says...

92
00:05:45,750 --> 00:05:47,541
And that's all I have
for the moment regarding

93
00:05:47,625 --> 00:05:50,666
our Hotel Createur
Tokyo. Let's move on now to

94
00:05:50,750 --> 00:05:53,375
the situation with the
west side of Amamizu Station,

95
00:05:53,458 --> 00:05:56,416
where construction is
planned. We are in continuing

96
00:05:56,500 --> 00:05:58,958
negotiations with the residents
so that we can break ground

97
00:05:59,041 --> 00:06:02,041
the year after next at the
latest. The site purchase is

98
00:06:02,125 --> 00:06:04,416
proceeding on schedule
and shouldn't encounter any

99
00:06:04,500 --> 00:06:07,791
major delays as the project goes
forward over the coming months.

100
00:06:07,875 --> 00:06:10,750
That's no good. Amamizu-kan
is right in the middle of the

101
00:06:10,833 --> 00:06:14,958
proposed site. What'll Tsukimi
do once the buyout is final?

102
00:06:17,166 --> 00:06:18,666
