133
00:08:10,666 --> 00:08:14,958
Do not get in our way! Special
Attack: "Take money and go eat!"

134
00:08:16,083 --> 00:08:18,833
Ichiyo Higuchi!

135
00:08:19,791 --> 00:08:21,333
We're going to Chinatown!

136
00:08:21,416 --> 00:08:23,666
The Minatomirai Line is mine!

137
00:08:23,750 --> 00:08:24,875
It's Chinatown, Jake!

138
00:08:24,958 --> 00:08:26,666
And extra batteries!

139
00:08:27,333 --> 00:08:29,208
So... where were we?

140
00:08:38,208 --> 00:08:39,791
Now... Scissors!

141
00:08:39,875 --> 00:08:41,166
I-I don't--

142
00:08:41,250 --> 00:08:44,166
It doesn't have to be exact.
Just cut around me...

143
00:08:44,250 --> 00:08:46,166
try to make it
somewhat dress-shaped.

144
00:08:46,250 --> 00:08:48,291
If it doesn't work, try again.

145
00:08:48,375 --> 00:08:51,416
Okay, Mom. What is
it that makes me think

146
00:08:51,500 --> 00:08:55,500
this strange guy is so
beautiful? Maybe it's because

147
00:08:55,583 --> 00:08:59,000
his arms and legs
are so pale and slender.

148
00:08:59,458 --> 00:09:01,541
He's just like a jellyfish.

149
00:09:06,208 --> 00:09:08,083
Make it like
that whatsit-jelly.

150
00:09:08,166 --> 00:09:09,791
It's called a
"Flower Hat Jelly."

151
00:09:09,875 --> 00:09:11,333
Yeah, that.

152
00:09:12,125 --> 00:09:16,166
Looking at this beautiful young
man... he fills my heart with...

153
00:09:16,250 --> 00:09:20,416
I don't know... like my heart
is filled with jellyfish lace...

154
00:09:20,500 --> 00:09:22,125
It's almost enough
to make me forget

155
00:09:22,208 --> 00:09:24,791
all the bad things
that have happened.

156
00:09:26,041 --> 00:09:27,416
Good afternoon!

157
00:09:27,500 --> 00:09:28,500
Hello.

158
00:09:28,583 --> 00:09:30,291
What're you up to after this?

159
00:09:30,375 --> 00:09:32,333
Back to the office.
I have to write up all the

160
00:09:32,416 --> 00:09:34,208
details from the meeting.

161
00:09:43,916 --> 00:09:44,833
Where're we going?

162
00:09:44,916 --> 00:09:46,375
Get out of the car.

163
00:09:46,458 --> 00:09:47,041
Let's go to--

164
00:09:47,125 --> 00:09:48,416
Please get out!

165
00:09:49,333 --> 00:09:52,041
What exactly do
you want from me?!

166
00:09:52,125 --> 00:09:56,666
I get it now. So I was no more
than a one-night stand for you.

167
00:09:56,750 --> 00:09:58,333
Have it your way.

168
00:09:58,416 --> 00:10:02,750
If that's what you want...
I'll just disappear... forever.

169
00:10:02,833 --> 00:10:04,416
Elite Man Snaring Techniques,

170
00:10:04,500 --> 00:10:06,541
Inari-Style:
A Beginners' Course.

171
00:10:06,625 --> 00:10:09,666
If pushing doesn't work, try
guilt ridden pulling him along.

172
00:10:09,750 --> 00:10:12,333
I guarantee he'll call
in the next two or three days.

173
00:10:12,416 --> 00:10:13,916
Please don't go.

174
00:10:14,000 --> 00:10:16,583
That was fast! Guess I should
expect as much from a virgin.

175
00:10:16,666 --> 00:10:18,625
He's got the resolve
of a middle schooler.

176
00:10:18,708 --> 00:10:20,583
But watch how I
boldly ignore him.

177
00:10:20,666 --> 00:10:22,125
Taxi!

178
00:10:22,208 --> 00:10:23,958
No wait! Please!

179
00:10:30,583 --> 00:10:31,500
Commercial message!

180
00:10:31,583 --> 00:10:32,708
Clara!

181
00:10:34,000 --> 00:10:34,875
Now the other part!

182
00:10:34,958 --> 00:10:36,208
Tequila.

183
00:10:37,750 --> 00:10:40,541
Down to 5 hundred 35 yen?
Dang, Madam Ichiyo didn't even

