bit more like a bell now.

229
00:12:46,166 --> 00:12:48,750
Hey, you're right. Not bad.

230
00:12:48,833 --> 00:12:51,333
Chieko, could you sew
it on the machine for me?

231
00:12:51,416 --> 00:12:54,208
No problem. But what do you
want me to do with the edges?

232
00:12:54,291 --> 00:12:56,333
All your margins
on the outside.

233
00:12:56,416 --> 00:12:59,458
I really don't care. Long
as it's shaped like a bell,

234
00:12:59,541 --> 00:13:00,958
that's good enough for me.

235
00:13:01,041 --> 00:13:03,791
It's a good start, but I don't
think it'll get that shape

236
00:13:03,875 --> 00:13:05,666
unless I wear
a pannier underneath.

237
00:13:05,750 --> 00:13:07,208
Pa... what?

238
00:13:07,291 --> 00:13:10,166
"Pannier..." That thing
all the Goth-Lolis wear

239
00:13:10,250 --> 00:13:13,375
under their skirts... Y'know,
like a ballerina's tutu.

240
00:13:13,458 --> 00:13:15,166
Sure... I knew that.

241
00:13:15,250 --> 00:13:17,791
Oh hey, let's go
finish this at my place.

242
00:13:17,875 --> 00:13:20,291
I've got a bunch
there. My bro's gone.

243
00:13:20,375 --> 00:13:23,583
And there's no one else
to interrupt us. It's perfect.

244
00:13:23,666 --> 00:13:24,750
O-kay...

245
00:13:37,208 --> 00:13:38,541
Tsukimi?

246
00:13:41,041 --> 00:13:41,875
Chieko?

247
00:13:41,958 --> 00:13:42,875
Yes?

248
00:13:42,958 --> 00:13:44,208
You like all
sorts of old stuff.

249
00:13:44,291 --> 00:13:45,666
How'd you like to
take a bunch of pictures

250
00:13:45,750 --> 00:13:46,958
of a cool old mansion?

251
00:13:47,041 --> 00:13:48,750
Actually, I love old houses.

252
00:13:48,833 --> 00:13:49,791
I recently went to a

253
00:13:49,875 --> 00:13:51,916
Western-style
house in Kamakura...

254
00:13:52,000 --> 00:13:52,958
Look.

255
00:13:54,208 --> 00:13:55,166
Wow!

256
00:13:55,250 --> 00:13:57,250
Could I ask you
for one more favor?

257
00:13:59,541 --> 00:14:02,958
Perfect, thanks! This
is totes going on my blog.

258
00:14:03,041 --> 00:14:04,500
Buh... Blog?

259
00:14:04,583 --> 00:14:07,583
Afros are just so scrunchy.
Where did you get yours done?

260
00:14:07,666 --> 00:14:09,166
Ah-oh-yama? It was, huh?

261
00:14:09,250 --> 00:14:11,000
Uhh... I was born this way.

262
00:14:11,083 --> 00:14:13,458
I've always thought
they were totally retro cool.

263
00:14:13,541 --> 00:14:15,583
But my agency
won't let me get one!

264
00:14:15,666 --> 00:14:19,375
One more feel
please? It's so animal!

265
00:14:20,291 --> 00:14:24,291
So this is it. Not such
a bad place, I guess.

266
00:14:25,916 --> 00:14:31,083
Excuse me, sir! Do you know
where I can find this address?

267
00:14:31,166 --> 00:14:33,916
Uhh... that place, huh?

268
00:14:34,583 --> 00:14:39,708
Dang... Why do those guys always
make me drink so damn much?

269
00:14:39,791 --> 00:14:44,000
And who the hell orders
Dom Pérignon Rosé these days?!

270
00:14:44,625 --> 00:14:48,833
Twelve messages...
What's a girl to do?

271
00:14:49,625 --> 00:14:52,458
Wow, this salami's good.

272
00:14:54,166 --> 00:14:57,041
It's ringing again!
I'm not here...

273
00:14:57,125 --> 00:14:59,291
but I'll answer... speak.

274
00:14:59,375 --> 00:15:01,541
Hi, it's Shu--Koibuchi.

275
00:15:01,625 --> 00:15:04,916
I believe I said I wouldn't
talk to you anymore, didn't I?

276
00:15:05,000 --> 00:15:07,791
Well, yeah,
but I just thought.

277
00:15:07,875 --> 00:15:09,166
Oh crap.

278
00:15:09,250 --> 00:15:10,333
Excuse me?

279
00:15:10,416 --> 00:15:13,083
I've had too much.
My head's all fuzzy...

280
00:15:14,208 --> 00:15:19,166
It's getting dark.
I'm over. Nice knowing you.

281
00:15:19,250 --> 00:15:22,708
What's that? Too much
what? Talk to me... Hello?

282
00:15:22,791 --> 00:15:25,583
What have you--? You didn't go
and do anything stupid did you?

283
00:15:25,666 --> 00:15:27,250
I'll be right there.

284
00:15:27,333 --> 00:15:31,833
What a dork. He's gotta be
joking. As if I'd kill myself

285
00:15:31,916 --> 00:15:34,916
because I couldn't
have Mr. Promise Keeper.

286
00:15:35,000 --> 00:15:37,541
Virgins are such
a pain in the ass.

287
00:15:47,250 --> 00:15:50,208
Oh! Taisho Romance!

288
00:15:52,375 --> 00:15:54,958
Jackpot! It's
a treasure trove!

289
00:15:55,041 --> 00:15:56,958
I told you we had
a crap-ton of pictures of

290
00:15:57,041 --> 00:15:59,166
old dead dudes
hanging everywhere.

291
00:16:01,750 --> 00:16:03,333
Now are you ready to
come out of your shell

292
00:16:03,416 --> 00:16:06,666
and help me with the
dress? We can do this.

293
00:16:08,583 --> 00:16:09,708
Talk to me.

294
00:16:11,166 --> 00:16:12,708
Please let me go home.

295
00:16:12,791 --> 00:16:16,458
Why are you being so silly? My
brother's not here. I told you.

296
00:16:16,541 --> 00:16:20,375
It's not him... it's--
I don't like the way I feel...

297
00:16:21,000 --> 00:16:22,875
I get all heated
up over stuff and then

298
00:16:22,958 --> 00:16:24,833
I go cold all of a sudden...

299
00:16:24,916 --> 00:16:27,666
I'm sick of it.
Too confusing.

300
00:16:27,750 --> 00:16:30,541
I want my life
just to be lukewarm.

301
00:16:31,250 --> 00:16:35,583
Okay, here it is... I want
to take this jellyfish you drew

302
00:16:35,666 --> 00:16:40,375
and make it real...
I want to see that... got it?

303
00:16:41,375 --> 00:16:43,041
But why?

304
00:16:43,625 --> 00:16:45,041
It's beautiful.

305
00:16:45,125 --> 00:16:48,458
I am truly impressed!
And look...

306
00:16:48,541 --> 00:16:50,291
another picture perfect room.

307
00:16:50,375 --> 00:16:51,583
It's wonderful!

308
00:16:53,500 --> 00:16:54,500
Be careful.

309
00:16:54,583 --> 00:16:57,541
I'm so sorry! I
got over-excited...

310
00:16:57,625 --> 00:17:00,666
That's okay. It's totally
cute, right? I love it.

311
00:17:00,750 --> 00:17:04,625
This room is divine! I wish I'd
brought Midoriko and the others!

312
00:17:04,708 --> 00:17:08,833
I wonder... If I could somehow
give the feeling of that moment

313
00:17:08,916 --> 00:17:14,750
in life, not just in a drawing,
but also in real life...

314
00:17:14,833 --> 00:17:17,458
a shape, with
my own two hands...

315
00:17:20,208 --> 00:17:21,291
Hey, Tsuki...

316
00:17:22,583 --> 00:17:24,583
Jiji... Chieko...

317
00:17:25,458 --> 00:17:27,208
Lend me your aid!

318
00:17:45,041 --> 00:17:46,208
No!

319
00:17:50,583 --> 00:17:53,875
Psych! In your face!
Were you scared?

320
00:17:53,958 --> 00:17:56,083
'Cause these are
just my vitamins.

321
00:18:01,166 --> 00:18:02,250
What?

322
00:18:06,583 --> 00:18:10,458
Ow, hey, stop it! Ow, ah ow! Ah!

323
00:18:12,000 --> 00:18:14,958
It was just a stupid joke
there's no reason to freak--

324
00:18:33,250 --> 00:18:35,500
Wow hey, that
was awfully quick.

325
00:18:35,583 --> 00:18:38,458
I, guess she was
dead. Your getaway car.

326
00:18:39,125 --> 00:18:40,291
Take me to the
airport, please.

327
00:18:40,375 --> 00:18:41,541
Skippin' town entirely?

328
00:18:41,625 --> 00:18:43,000
Let's go. Now.

329
00:18:43,083 --> 00:18:44,208
Yessir.

330
00:18:46,375 --> 00:18:48,666
She wasn't dead, thank god.

331
00:18:49,750 --> 00:18:51,416
I'm finished over here.

332
00:18:51,500 --> 00:18:54,250
Okay, what about
over on this side?

333
00:18:56,625 --> 00:18:58,958
Oh boy... I fell asleep.

334
00:18:59,041 --> 00:19:01,125
These pearls are
beautiful, though, aren't they?

335
00:19:01,208 --> 00:19:03,750
They're fakes but
they're high quality fakes.

336
00:19:03,833 --> 00:19:05,875
I think I want a
little more down here.

337
00:19:05,958 --> 00:19:08,208
That's... whoa...

338
00:19:08,291 --> 00:19:09,458
All done.

339
00:19:15,250 --> 00:19:18,333
We finally finished! The
day is saved thanks to...

340
00:19:18,416 --> 00:19:20,750
The Sisterhood
Human Wave Attack!

341
00:19:21,833 --> 00:19:24,250
Fine detail work always
gets to my shoulders!

342
00:19:24,333 --> 00:19:28,375
I could get the Kita no Kuni
Kara DVD box set as my reward.

343
00:19:34,125 --> 00:19:36,083
Oh my god, hot!

344
00:19:36,166 --> 00:19:38,458
Yeah... the
Flower Hat Jelly's the

345
00:19:38,541 --> 00:19:41,416
pop idol of
the jellyfish world.

346
00:19:41,500 --> 00:19:44,291
I think the tentacles
came out really nicely, too.

347
00:19:45,166 --> 00:19:48,125
Hey... can I... try it on?

348
00:19:49,166 --> 00:19:52,916
Oh, yeah. Tsukimi
tore apart the necklace.

349
00:19:53,000 --> 00:19:55,958
But uh, they are fakes, right?

350
00:19:56,041 --> 00:19:58,708
Yeah no, they're real.
Probably worth a few million...

351
00:19:58,791 --> 00:20:02,000
What?! Then each pearl
is at least ten thousand?!

352
00:20:02,083 --> 00:20:04,541
I'm so sorry I broke
your necklace. I just--

353
00:20:04,625 --> 00:20:07,166
I thought they looked perfect
for a jellyfish's tentacles

354
00:20:07,250 --> 00:20:10,166
especially the ones on
a Flower Hat. I'm sorry.

355
00:20:10,250 --> 00:20:11,416
It's okay.

356
00:20:12,833 --> 00:20:15,000
I'm sure it would make
my mom happy to see this...

357
00:20:15,083 --> 00:20:17,208
She always
loved pretty dresses.

358
00:20:18,750 --> 00:20:23,875
Mama... What if...
What if I were a girl?

359
00:20:24,750 --> 00:20:26,250
I'll give you these, too...

360
00:20:26,333 --> 00:20:29,083
I got them from your
papa a long time ago.

361
00:20:29,875 --> 00:20:30,916
Yeah?

362
00:20:32,958 --> 00:20:35,750
Sometimes I really
wish you were a girl.

363
00:20:35,833 --> 00:20:38,208
Then your Papa
would understand better.

364
00:20:39,416 --> 00:20:42,750
If only I'd been born as
the perfect little princess.

365
00:20:42,833 --> 00:20:47,666
Maybe... maybe then I could
have stayed with my mom forever.

366
00:20:57,125 --> 00:20:59,291
Never expected
we'd stay out all night.

367
00:20:59,375 --> 00:21:01,833
Your fault again for not getting
out of the electric bath

368
00:21:01,916 --> 00:21:03,625
in time for the last train.

369
00:21:03,708 --> 00:21:06,666
Sorry! I just kinda figured
shock therapy would be

370
00:21:06,750 --> 00:21:08,083
the best way to zap away

371
00:21:08,166 --> 00:21:11,458
any Stylish juice
that got on us. Huh?

372
00:21:19,166 --> 00:21:20,791
What's goin' on?

373
00:21:20,875 --> 00:21:25,625
It's over! Baidi's been
conquered. It can't be!

